{"word":"δόσις","slug":"δόσις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>δόσις, εως, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δώσω\">δώσω</a></el>, the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ fut.\">fut.</a> of <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δίδωμι\">δίδωμι</a></el>, and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ s.\">s.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δότης\">δότης</a></el>]<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> as act: <b><i>giving</i> <a href='B:570 4:15'>Phil 4:15</a></b> <el>δ. ϰαὶ λήμψις</el>, commercial term, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> our ‘debit and credit’, but <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> awareness of Hellenistic nuance of reciprocity<b>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> as object: <b><i>gift</i> <a href='B:660 1:17'>Js 1:17</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:δός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:δότης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}